properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 14 at 11:41AM MST until February 14 at 9:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...Significant Blowing Snow Today across portions of Central
Wyoming...

...Winter Storm Watch for Far Western Wyoming Saturday Night
through Sunday night...

.A combination of strong wind and fresh snow will result in
considerable blowing and drifting of snow across southern Fremont
County into Natrona County this afternoon. A strong storm system
will likely bring significant snow across far western Wyoming
Saturday night through Sunday evening.

* WHAT...Areas of blowing and drifting of snow. Southwest wind of
30 to 40 mph with gusts from 50 to 65 mph. Locally higher winds
near 80 mph in the Red Canyon area.

* WHERE...South Pass.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM.

* IMPACTS...Travel over South Pass will remain very difficult to
nearly impossible. The combination of strong wind and slippery
roads will increase the chances of a vehicle sliding off the
road.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Localized whiteout conditions possible.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM MST THIS EVENING
